               │ Healthy │    │ Healthy │   │ Healthy │
               └─────────┘    └─────────┘   └─────────┘
          💡 Why Use ELB?

🔀 Types of ELB
AWS provides 4 types of Load Balancers:
====================================================================================================
1️⃣ ALB — Application Load Balancer
              Layer 7 (HTTP/HTTPS) — Smartest load balancer
              
              How it works:
              
              Looks at the content of the request (URL, headers, cookies)
              Routes traffic based on rules
              Users
                │
                ▼
              ALB
                │
                ├── /api/*        → EC2 (API Servers)
                ├── /images/*     → EC2 (Image Servers)
                ├── /login/*      → EC2 (Auth Servers)
                └── /checkout/*   → EC2 (Payment Servers)
              Real Time Example:
              Amazon.com:
              User visits /products → ALB routes to Product Service EC2
              User visits /cart → ALB routes to Cart Service EC2
              User visits /payment → ALB routes to Payment Service EC2
              All under one domain amazon.com ✅
              Use Cases:
              
              Microservices architecture
              Container-based applications
              HTTP/HTTPS web applications
              Path-based and host-based routing
              Table
              
              
              Feature	Details
              Protocol	HTTP, HTTPS, WebSocket
              Layer	Layer 7 (Application)
              Routing	URL path, hostname, headers, query strings
              Target	EC2, Lambda, IP, Containers
              Best For	Web apps, microservices
========================================================================================================
2️⃣ NLB — Network Load Balancer
          Layer 4 (TCP/UDP) — Fastest load balancer
          How it works:
          Does NOT look at content
          Routes based on IP and Port only
          Handles millions of requests per second
          Users
            │
            ▼
          NLB (Ultra Fast ⚡)
            │
            ├── TCP Port 80  → EC2 #1
            ├── TCP Port 443 → EC2 #2
            └── UDP Port 53  → EC2 #3
          (Routes by IP + Port only — no content inspection)
          Real Time Example:
          Online Gaming (PUBG/Fortnite):
                    Millions of players connect simultaneously
                    NLB handles millions of TCP/UDP connections per second
                    Ultra-low latency required ⚡
                    No need to inspect content — just route fast
          Use Cases:
                    Gaming applications
                    IoT applications
                    Real-time streaming
                    Anything needing ultra-low latency
          Table        
          Feature	Details
          Protocol	TCP, UDP, TLS
          Layer	Layer 4 (Transport)
          Routing	IP + Port only
          Speed	Millions of req/sec ⚡
          Best For	Gaming, IoT, streaming
=============================================================================================
3️⃣ GLB — Gateway Load Balancer  : Layer 3 (IP) — Security focused load balancer

          How it works:
                    Routes traffic through third-party security appliances
                    Inspect ALL traffic before it reaches your app
                    Acts as a security gateway
          Users
            │
            ▼
          GLB (Gateway Load Balancer)
            │
            ▼
          Security Appliances
            ├── Firewall Check
            ├── Intrusion Detection
            └── Deep Packet Inspection
            │
            ▼
          EC2 Instances (Only clean traffic reaches here) ✅
          Real Time Example:
          Bank or Financial Institution:
                    ALL incoming traffic must pass through security checks
                    Firewall inspects every packet
                    Intrusion detection system scans for attacks
                    Only safe traffic reaches the banking application ✅
          Use Cases:
          Network security
          Firewall management
          Intrusion detection
          Deep packet inspection

          Table
          Feature	Details
          Protocol	IP (Layer 3)
          Layer	Layer 3 (Network)
          Routing	All IP traffic
          Best For	Security appliances
========================================================================================
4️⃣ CLB — Classic Load Balancer
                    Layer 4 + 7 — Old generation (Deprecated ⚠️)
                    How it works:
                    
                    Old generation load balancer
                    Supports both HTTP and TCP
                    Not recommended for new applications
                    Users
                      │
                      ▼
                    CLB (Old Generation ⚠️)
                      │
                      ├── HTTP  → EC2 #1
                      └── TCP   → EC2 #2
                    (Basic routing only)
                    ⚠️ AWS recommends using ALB or NLB instead of CLB

